SI 201 Final Project Plan

a. What is your group's name?

Melody Metrics 

b. Who are the people in the group (first name, last name, umich email for all members)?

Jerri Boyd jerrib@umich.edu 
Erin Proctor eproc@umich.edu

c. What APIs/websites will you be gathering data from? The base URLs for the APIs/websites must be different for them to count as different APIs.

Spotify API- https://developer.spotify.com/documentation/web-api
Last.fm API- https://www.last.fm/api/authentication 

d. What data will you collect from each API/website and store in a database? Be specific.

From Spotify:
Song name
Artist name
Release year
Album info
Primary genre
From Last.fm:
Global play count
Number of listeners
Tags (rock, R&B, EDM, etc.)
e. What data will you be calculating from the data in the database? Be specific.
Avg. popularity for each release decade (80s, 90s, 00s, 10s, 20s)
Most popular genres by decade
Song “longevity index” = plays / (2025 - release_year)

f. What visualization package will you be using (Matplotlib, Plotly, Seaborn, etc)?
Seaborn - to create a bar chart, scatterplot, and heatmap. 
Matplotlib- adjust formatting (size, title, labels, colors, etc)

g. What graphs/charts will you be creating?
Bar chart: popularity by decade
Scatter: release year vs play count
Heatmap: genre × decade popularity

h. What functions are you creating and who is responsible for each function?  What input and output does each function take?   Include a function diagram with this information on it.  

                           
     main.py                   
  (Runs the entire project workflow)              
               
   spotify_data.py                             
get_spotify_tracks(query) - Erin 
    Input: search term (artist, genre)
    Output: list of track metadata dictionaries
             
get_spotify_audio_features(track_ids) - Erin 
    Input: list of Spotify track IDs
    Output: audio feature data (tempo, energy, etc.)
                     
store_spotify_data(db_cursor, track_list, feature_list)-(Jerri)
    Input: database cursor, metadata + audio features
    Output: Inserts into tracks, artists, audio_features tables

lastfm_data.py                               
get_lastfm_stats(track_name, artist_name) - Erin 
    Input: track name, artist
    Output: listeners, playcount, top tag(s)
                
store_lastfm_data(db_cursor, stats) - Erin 
    Input: database cursor, Last.fm stats (linked via track_id)
    Output: Inserts into lastfm_stats table
                    
database.py                                 
connect_db(db_name) - Erin 
    Input: database filename
    Output: conn, cursor
                      
create_tables(cursor)(Jerri)
    Input: database cursor
    Output: SQLite tables created

analysis_visuals.py                              
calculate_popularity_by_decade(cursor) (Jerri)
    Input: SQL JOIN tracks + lastfm_stats
    Output: {decade: avg_popularity

calculate_listeners_by_decade(cursor) - Erin 
    Input: SQL JOIN across tables
    Output: {decade: avg_listeners}
               
calculate_genre_trends(cursor)
    Input: SQL JOIN tracks + artists + lastfm_stats(Jerri)
    Output: genre popularity per decade
         
plot_popularity_by_decade(data)(Jerri)
    Input: dictionary of decade→popularity
    Output: bar chart
            
plot_scatter_releaseyear_vs_listeners(data) - Erin 
    Input: paired lists (year, listeners)
    Output: scatter plot
       
plot_genre_trends(data)(Jerri)
    Input: genre × decade data
    Output: line graph
